HEADWORD: Thrall-like
<hw>Thrall"-like`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Resembling a
thrall, or his condition, feelings, or the like; slavish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Servile and <qex>thrall-like</qex> fear.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thranite</ent>⟦br⟧
